    <description>Line items for Payable
A payable line item represents a specific entry on a payable, offering a detailed breakdown of the total payable amount. 
Population Requirement Details: If the triggers are ON, the system will automatically create lines with line amounts for MR payable based on the supplemental Rent amount calculated on utilization and for Claims payable based on the claim amount for a partiluar fund . Security deposit and other types of payales will only have one line auto-created by the system.
If the trigger is OFF, the data for the payable line items must be manually loaded. However, this is not a recommended method for loading payable line data.
[MODULE: Finance]
[LOAD: Optional]
[PREREQUISITES: Payable (if loading with Triggers OFF)]
[REPLACEMENT OBJECT API: NA]
[COMMENTS: NA]</description>
